{"photo": {"people": {"haspeople": 0}, "dateuploaded": "1344588986", "originalformat": "jpg", "owner": {"username": "The National Archives UK", "realname": "", "nsid": "31575009@N05", "iconserver": "7325", "location": "", "path_alias": "nationalarchives", "iconfarm": 8}, "publiceditability": {"canaddmeta": 1, "cancomment": 1}, "id": "7751738690", "title": {"_content": "Riegner Telegram"}, "media": "photo", "tags": {"tag": [{"raw": "The National Archives (UK)", "machine_tag": 0, "id": "31569669-7751738690-30835915", "_content": "thenationalarchivesuk", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "Second World War", "machine_tag": 0, "id": "31569669-7751738690-142981", "_content": "secondworldwar", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "Foreign Office", "machine_tag": 0, "id": "31569669-7751738690-187878", "_content": "foreignoffice", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "tna:PieceReference=FO371p30917", "machine_tag": 1, "id": "31569669-7751738690-108884733", "_content": "tna:PieceReference=fo371p30917", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "tna:SubseriesReference=FO371ss225", "machine_tag": 1, "id": "31569669-7751738690-108884735", "_content": "tna:SubseriesReference=fo371ss225", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "tna:IAID=C2788141", "machine_tag": 1, "id": "31569669-7751738690-108884737", "_content": "tna:IAID=c2788141", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "tna:SeriesReference=FO371", "machine_tag": 1, "id": "31569669-7751738690-108877795", "_content": "tna:SeriesReference=fo371", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "tna:DivisionReference=FOd1", "machine_tag": 1, "id": "31569669-7751738690-108877797", "_content": "tna:DivisionReference=fod1", "author": "31575009@N05"}, {"raw": "tna:DepartmentReference=FO", "machine_tag": 1, "id": "31569669-7751738690-108877253", "_content": "tna:DepartmentReference=fo", "author": "31575009@N05"}]}, "comments": {"_content": "1"}, "secret": "17fe1f0527", "usage": {"canblog": 0, "canshare": 1, "candownload": 1, "canprint": 0}, "description": {"_content": "<b>Description:</b> This telegram from Gerhart Riegner, Secretary of the World Jewish Congress in Geneva, was received by the Foreign Office in August 1940. The telegram was among the first pieces of unambiguous evidence received by the Allies that the Nazi Government planned a 'final solution' to the &quot;Jewish question&quot;.\n\nSome comments within the file show officials suggested the telegram be used to influence the Vatican to condemn German atrocities more strenuously. Another civil servant dismisses Riegner's report as a &quot;rather wild story&quot;.\n\nSamuel Sydney Silverman, the telegram's intended recipient, was the Labour MP for the Lancashire constituency of Nelson and Colne. Silverman was a campaigner for Jewish rights, amongst other causes including opposition to capital punishment. \n\n<b>Date:</b> August 10th 1942\n\n<b>Our Catalogue Reference:</b> <a href=\"http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/SearchUI/Details?uri=C2788141\" rel=\"nofollow\">FO 371/30917</a>\n\nThis image is from the collections of The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons.\n\nFor high quality reproductions of any item from our collection please contact our <a href=\"http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/imagelibrary\" rel=\"nofollow\">image library</a>."}, "isfavorite": 0, "views": "2049", "farm": 9, "visibility": {"isfriend": 0, "isfamily": 0, "ispublic": 1}, "rotation": 0, "dates": {"taken": "2007-10-29 12:31:52", "lastupdate": "1370490242", "takengranularity": "0", "posted": "1344588986"}, "originalsecret": "7f520890e7", "license": "7", "notes": {"note": []}, "server": "8304", "safety_level": "0", "urls": {"url": [{"type": "photopage", "_content": "http://www.flickr.com/photos/nationalarchives/7751738690/"}]}, "editability": {"canaddmeta": 0, "cancomment": 0}}, "stat": "ok"}